<TITLE> Iran probing fourth US-Iranian </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TEHRAN, June 8 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Iran is investigating a fourth Iranian-American citizen detained on security-related accusations, Iran's ISNA news agency reported on Friday. Iran has charged two dual nationals with spying and a third is being investigated for "anti-revolutionary" activities. The United States has said Iran was holding Ali Shakeri, a Californian businessman, but until now Iran had not confirmed his case was being investigated. "The case of Ali Shakeri ... is now being investigated in the assistance office of Tehran's public prosecutor," ISNA reported adding the investigation involved "security-related charges"
